ALEXANDER ANDERSON, Inc., v. EASTMAN OIL WELL SURVEY COMPANY OF CALIFORNIA et al. No. 8763. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Feb. 7, 1938. Lyon & Lyon, of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellant. Hill, Morgan & Bledsoé and Joseph F. Westall, all of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellees.

Before WILBUR, MATHEWS, and STEPHENS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for respective parties, ordered appeal herein dismissed, that a decree of dismissal be filed and entered accordingly, and the mandate of this court issue forthwith.
